00:00:00:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:00:020000.Dialogue: On the other hand, some physicists are concerned that if this supercollider actually works, it'll create a black hole and swallow up the Earth, ending life as we know it.

00:00:08:110000.Speaker: Raj
00:00:08:110000.Dialogue: What a bunch of crybabies. No guts, no glory, man.

00:00:13:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:13:120000.Dialogue: Hey, check it out. The School of Pharmacology is looking for volunteers.

00:00:18:060000.Speaker: Raj
00:00:18:060000.Dialogue: We are testing a new medication for social anxiety, panic attacks, agoraphobia and obsessive compulsive disorder.

00:00:26:130000.Speaker: Raj
00:00:26:130000.Dialogue: Why would they be looking for test subjects here?

00:00:30:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:30:030000.Dialogue: I don't know, Raj. Maybe the comic book store doesn't have a bulletin board.

00:00:47:070000.Speaker: Howard
00:00:47:070000.Dialogue: I don't think so. I followed her here from the parking lot.

00:00:54:100000.Speaker: Howard
00:00:54:100000.Dialogue: Well, she's free to examine my briefs.

00:00:57:070000.Speaker: Howard
00:00:57:070000.Dialogue: I know, I'm disgusting. I should be punished... by her. Look, I did it again.

00:01:20:140000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:20:140000.Dialogue: Sorry I'm late. I'm working on a project that may take me up on the next space shuttle.

00:01:26:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:26:160000.Dialogue: How can you be late? I wasn't expecting you at all.

00:01:30:050000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:30:050000.Dialogue: Nobody ever expects me. Sometimes you just look and... Bam! Howard Wolowitz.

00:01:38:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:38:180000.Dialogue: All right. This is Missy. Missy, this is Leonard and Rajesh, and you've already met Howard.

00:01:50:010000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:50:010000.Dialogue: So, how do you two know each other?

00:01:52:130000.Speaker: Missy
00:01:52:130000.Dialogue: He once spent nine months with my legs wrapped around his head.

00:02:01:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:01:130000.Dialogue: She's my twin sister. She thinks she's funny, but frankly, I've never been able to see it.

00:02:06:100000.Speaker: Missy
00:02:06:100000.Dialogue: That's because you have no measurable sense of humor, Shelly.

00:02:09:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:09:100000.Dialogue: How exactly would one measure a sense of humor? A humormometer?

00:02:19:020000.Speaker: unknown
00:02:19:020000.Dialogue: Or, as the French say, très drôle.

00:02:22:060000.Speaker: Missy
00:02:22:060000.Dialogue: So let me see if I got this. Leonard, Howard and... I'm sorry, what was your name again?

00:03:20:200000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:20:200000.Dialogue: So Missy, what brings you all the way from Texas?

00:03:23:040000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:23:040000.Dialogue: Was it perhaps destiny? I think it was destiny.

00:03:25:190000.Speaker: Missy
00:03:25:190000.Dialogue: My friend's getting married at Disneyland tomorrow night.

00:03:33:040000.Speaker: Missy
00:03:33:040000.Dialogue: And I had to drop off some papers for Shelly to sign for my Dad's estate.

00:03:36:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:36:140000.Dialogue: The papers could've been mailed. Mom sent you to spy on me, didn't she?

00:03:40:060000.Speaker: Missy
00:03:40:060000.Dialogue: I guess that's why they call you a genius.

00:03:42:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:42:170000.Dialogue: They call me a genius because I'm a genius.

00:03:46:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:46:070000.Dialogue: {\pos(192,200)}Tell Mom that I currently weigh 165 pounds and that I'm having regular bowel movements.

00:03:57:060000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:57:060000.Dialogue: If the wedding's not until tomorrow, why don't you stay with us tonight?

00:04:00:220000.Speaker: Missy
00:04:00:220000.Dialogue: I don't think so. Shelly doesn't like company. Even as a little boy, he'd send his imaginary friends home at the end of the day.

00:04:07:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:07:210000.Dialogue: They were not friends. They were imaginary colleagues.

00:04:11:220000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:11:220000.Dialogue: Look, you're here. We have plenty of room.

00:04:18:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:18:130000.Dialogue: So what, I don't issue invitations to your mother.

00:04:22:100000.Speaker: Missy
00:04:22:100000.Dialogue: It would be nice not to have to drive to Anaheim in rush hour.

00:04:25:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:25:070000.Dialogue: And don't ever call me Shelly.

00:04:27:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:27:230000.Dialogue: So it's settled: you'll stay with us.

00:04:29:220000.Speaker: Howard
00:04:29:220000.Dialogue: Yeah, I'll walk you to your car. You're in structure 3, level C, right?

00:04:40:230000.Speaker: Missy
00:04:40:230000.Dialogue: So anyway, we're eight years old and Sheldon converts my Easy Bake Oven to some kind of high-powered furnace.

00:04:50:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:50:200000.Dialogue: I needed a place to fire ceramic semiconductor substrates for homemade integrated circuits.

00:04:55:200000.Speaker: Missy
00:04:55:200000.Dialogue: He was trying to build some sort of armed robot

00:04:58:000000.Speaker: Missy
00:04:58:000000.Dialogue: to keep me out of his room.

00:04:59:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:59:180000.Dialogue: Made necessary by her insistence on going into my room.

00:05:03:110000.Speaker: Missy
00:05:03:110000.Dialogue: Anyway, I go to make those little corn muffins they give you. There's a big flash. Next thing you know my eyebrows are gone.

00:05:13:140000.Speaker: Missy
00:05:13:140000.Dialogue: Yep, I had to go through the entire second grade with crooked eyebrows my mom drew on.

00:05:18:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:18:210000.Dialogue: Is that what that was? I just assumed that the second grade curriculum had rendered you quizzical.

00:05:27:170000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:27:170000.Dialogue: You left your underwear in the dryer downstairs.

00:05:39:150000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:39:150000.Dialogue: Really? They have your little name label in them.

00:05:43:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:05:43:230000.Dialogue: Yeah, no, I do... I use those... just to polish up my spearfishing equipment.

00:05:57:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:05:57:120000.Dialogue: When I'm not crossbow hunting, I spearfish.

00:06:03:090000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:03:090000.Dialogue: This is Sheldon's twin sister, Missy. This is our neighbor, Penny.

00:06:07:080000.Speaker: Penny
00:06:07:080000.Dialogue: You don't look that much alike.

00:06:14:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:14:030000.Dialogue: They are no more alike than any other siblings.

00:06:19:010000.Speaker: Raj
00:06:19:010000.Dialogue: Hey, guess what. I've been accepted as a test subject for a new miracle drug to overcome pathological shyness.

00:06:39:130000.Speaker: Raj
00:06:39:130000.Dialogue: They mentioned there may be side effects.

00:06:44:020000.Speaker: Raj
00:06:44:020000.Dialogue: So, Missy, have you ever met a man from the exotic subcontinent of India?

00:06:50:210000.Speaker: Missy
00:06:50:210000.Dialogue: Well, there's Dr. Patel at our church.

00:06:55:140000.Speaker: Howard
00:06:55:140000.Dialogue: Do you like motorcycles? 'Cause I ride a hog.

00:06:59:050000.Speaker: Raj
00:06:59:050000.Dialogue: A hog? You have a two-cylinder scooter with a basket in the front.

00:07:04:070000.Speaker: Howard
00:07:04:070000.Dialogue: You still have to wear a helmet.

00:07:08:070000.Speaker: Raj
00:07:08:070000.Dialogue: Have you ever heard of the Kama Sutra?

00:07:13:130000.Speaker: Raj
00:07:13:130000.Dialogue: In other words, if you wonder, wonder who wrote the book of love, it was us.

00:07:20:100000.Speaker: Penny
00:07:20:100000.Dialogue: Sheldon's sister is pretty cute, huh?

00:07:25:160000.Speaker: Penny
00:07:25:160000.Dialogue: I didn't say you were. I just said she was cute.

00:07:30:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:30:120000.Dialogue: Maybe, if you like women who are tall... and perfect.

00:07:39:160000.Speaker: Penny
00:07:39:160000.Dialogue: Sheldon, why are you ignoring your sister?

00:07:41:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:41:220000.Dialogue: I'm not ignoring my sister. I'm ignoring all of you.

00:08:10:090000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:10:090000.Dialogue: Yeah, well, my people invented circumcision.

00:08:20:220000.Speaker: Penny
00:08:20:220000.Dialogue: Missy, I'm gonna go get my nails done. Do you want to come?

00:08:36:100000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:36:100000.Dialogue: You two have to back off.

00:08:38:020000.Speaker: Raj
00:08:38:020000.Dialogue: Why should I back off? You back off, dude.

00:08:40:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:40:030000.Dialogue: Excuse me, this is my apartment, and she's my roommate's sister.

00:08:42:200000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:42:200000.Dialogue: So what? You've already got Penny!

00:08:52:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:52:090000.Dialogue: Excuse me. Can I interject something? I'm ordering pizza online. Is everyone okay with pepperoni?

00:09:01:160000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:01:160000.Dialogue: Sheldon, can I talk to you in private?

00:09:14:020000.Speaker: Howard
00:09:14:020000.Dialogue: I'm a fancy Indian man. We invented pajamas.

00:09:17:210000.Speaker: Raj
00:09:17:210000.Dialogue: Hey, look at me. I don't have a foreskin.

00:09:31:090000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:31:090000.Dialogue: Are you aware that your sister is an incredibly attractive woman?

00:09:37:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:37:100000.Dialogue: She certainly has the symmetry and low body fat that Western culture deems desirable.

00:09:42:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:42:030000.Dialogue: Sheldon’s bedroom. heavier women were the standard for beauty because their girth suggested affluence.

00:09:51:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:51:040000.Dialogue: I didn't say it was fascinating. I said it was noteworthy.

00:09:57:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:57:050000.Dialogue: But my point is that Koothrappali and Wolowitz, they're hitting on your sister.

00:10:06:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:06:230000.Dialogue: Okay. You know, I don't want to criticize your rhetorical style, but we'd be a lot further along in this conversation if you'd begun with that thought.

00:10:15:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:15:090000.Dialogue: I'm saying we took quite an unnecessary detour from what I now understand to be your thesis.

00:10:22:160000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:22:160000.Dialogue: You have to do something about it.

00:10:28:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:28:170000.Dialogue: I don't understand. Yes, we shared a uterus for nine months,

00:10:33:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:33:040000.Dialogue: but since then we've pretty much gone our own separate ways.

00:10:37:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:37:050000.Dialogue: Okay, consider this. With your father gone, it is your responsibility to make sure that Missy chooses a suitable mate.

00:10:48:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:48:150000.Dialogue: I hadn't considered that. We do share DNA. So there is the possibility, however remote, that resting in her loins is the potential for another individual as remarkable as myself.

00:11:01:200000.Speaker: Leonard
00:11:01:200000.Dialogue: Exactly. And you owe it to yourself and to posterity to protect the genetic integrity of your sister's future offspring.

00:11:13:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:13:000000.Dialogue: You're right. If someone wants to get at Missy's Fallopian tubes, they'll have to go through me.

00:11:28:090000.Scene: The living room. Raj and Howard are on the floor, fighting.
00:11:28:090000.Speaker: Raj
00:11:28:090000.Dialogue: I am Shiva the Destroyer! I will have the woman.

00:11:33:120000.Scene: The living room. Raj and Howard are on the floor, fighting.
00:11:33:120000.Speaker: Howard
00:11:33:120000.Dialogue: I'm warning you, I was judo champion at math camp.

00:11:37:160000.Scene: The living room. Raj and Howard are on the floor, fighting.
00:11:37:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:37:160000.Dialogue: All right, now that's enough juvenile squabbling. You stop it. Stop it, I say!

00:11:43:080000.Scene: The living room. Raj and Howard are on the floor, fighting.
00:11:43:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:43:080000.Dialogue: I'm going to settle this right now. Neither of you are good enough for my sister.

00:11:48:040000.Scene: The living room. Raj and Howard are on the floor, fighting.
00:11:48:040000.Speaker: Howard
00:11:48:040000.Dialogue: Who are you to decide that?

00:11:49:220000.Scene: The living room. Raj and Howard are on the floor, fighting.
00:11:49:220000.Speaker: Leonard
00:11:49:220000.Dialogue: He's the man of his family. You have to respect his wishes.

00:11:53:000000.Scene: The living room. Raj and Howard are on the floor, fighting.
00:11:53:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:53:000000.Dialogue: You're out, too, by the way.

00:11:55:090000.Scene: The living room. Raj and Howard are on the floor, fighting.
00:11:55:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:55:090000.Dialogue: It's nothing personal. I'd just prefer if my future niece or nephew didn't become flatulent every time they ate an eskimo pie.

00:12:08:010000.Scene: The living room. Raj and Howard are on the floor, fighting.
00:12:08:010000.Speaker: Howard
00:12:08:010000.Dialogue: What are you so happy about?

00:12:09:230000.Scene: The living room. Raj and Howard are on the floor, fighting.
00:12:09:230000.Speaker: Raj
00:12:09:230000.Dialogue: I'm not happy. It's the medication. I can't stop smiling.

00:12:19:170000.Scene: The living room. Raj and Howard are on the floor, fighting.
00:12:19:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:19:170000.Dialogue: Now that Leonard's made me aware how high the genetic stakes are... we have to face the fact that none of you are suitable mates for my sister.

00:12:26:180000.Scene: The living room. Raj and Howard are on the floor, fighting.
00:12:26:180000.Speaker: Howard
00:12:26:180000.Dialogue: Wait a minute. Leonard made you aware of that?

00:12:31:020000.Scene: The living room. Raj and Howard are on the floor, fighting.
00:12:31:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:31:020000.Dialogue: We all make mistakes. Let's move on.

00:12:33:220000.Scene: The living room. Raj and Howard are on the floor, fighting.
00:12:33:220000.Speaker: Raj
00:12:33:220000.Dialogue: Excuse me, I think you're missing a big opportunity here.

00:12:36:120000.Scene: The living room. Raj and Howard are on the floor, fighting.
00:12:36:120000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:12:37:110000.Scene: The living room. Raj and Howard are on the floor, fighting.
00:12:37:110000.Speaker: Raj
00:12:37:110000.Dialogue: Everybody knows genetic diversity produces the strongest offspring.

00:12:41:040000.Scene: The living room. Raj and Howard are on the floor, fighting.
00:12:41:040000.Speaker: Raj
00:12:41:040000.Dialogue: Why not put a little mocha in the family latte?

00:12:47:110000.Scene: The living room. Raj and Howard are on the floor, fighting.
00:12:47:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:47:110000.Dialogue: In principle, you have a point. But as a practical matter, need I remind you that it takes experimental pharmaceuticals to simply enable you to speak to the opposite sex.

00:12:57:010000.Scene: The living room. Raj and Howard are on the floor, fighting.
00:12:57:010000.Speaker: Raj
00:12:57:010000.Dialogue: I think you're focusing entirely too much on the drugs.

00:13:06:050000.Scene: The living room. Raj and Howard are on the floor, fighting.
00:13:06:050000.Speaker: Howard
00:13:06:050000.Dialogue: Is it 'cause I'm Jewish? 'Cause I'd kill my rabbi with a pork chop to be with your sister.

00:13:17:100000.Scene: The living room. Raj and Howard are on the floor, fighting.
00:13:17:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:17:100000.Dialogue: This has nothing to do with religion. This has to do with the fact that you're a tiny, tiny man who still lives with his mother.

00:13:24:210000.Scene: The living room. Raj and Howard are on the floor, fighting.
00:13:24:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:24:210000.Dialogue: Sheldon, you are really being unreasonable.

00:13:27:080000.Scene: The living room. Raj and Howard are on the floor, fighting.
00:13:27:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:27:080000.Dialogue: Am I? Here, eat this cheese without farting and you can sleep with my sister.

00:13:34:020000.Scene: The living room. Raj and Howard are on the floor, fighting.
00:13:34:020000.Speaker: Missy

00:13:42:100000.Scene: The living room. Raj and Howard are on the floor, fighting.
00:13:42:100000.Speaker: Missy
00:13:42:100000.Dialogue: Shelly, can I speak to you for a minute? Alone.

00:13:46:070000.Scene: The living room. Raj and Howard are on the floor, fighting.
00:13:46:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:46:070000.Dialogue: Why does everyone suddenly want to talk to me alone? Usually nobody wants to be alone with me.

00:13:57:140000.Scene: The living room. Raj and Howard are on the floor, fighting.
00:13:57:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:57:140000.Dialogue: We all make mistakes. Let's move on.

00:14:03:070000.Speaker: Missy
00:14:03:070000.Dialogue: I'm not even going to ask why you're pimping me out for cheese.

00:14:07:180000.Speaker: Missy
00:14:07:180000.Dialogue: But since when do you care at all about who I sleep with?

00:14:11:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:11:130000.Dialogue: Truthfully, I've never given it any thought, but it has been pointed out to me that you carry DNA of great potential.

00:14:17:090000.Speaker: Missy
00:14:17:090000.Dialogue: What on earth are you talking about?

00:14:28:110000.Speaker: Missy
00:14:28:110000.Dialogue: And what do you mean, mediocre stock?

00:14:33:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:33:210000.Dialogue: But residing within you, is the potential for another me. Perhaps even taller, smarter, and less prone to freckling, a Sheldon 2.0, if you will.

00:14:46:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:46:100000.Dialogue: Exactly. Now, I am not saying that I should be the sole decider of who you mate with. If you're not attracted to the suitor, the likelihood of conception will be reduced.

00:14:55:170000.Speaker: Missy
00:14:55:170000.Dialogue: You have got to be kidding me.

00:15:02:110000.Speaker: Missy
00:15:02:110000.Dialogue: Okay, Shelly, sit down. Now I've lived my whole life dealing with the fact that my twin brother is, as mom puts it, one of God's special, little people.

00:15:16:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:16:120000.Dialogue: I always thought I was more like a cuckoo bird. You know, a superior creature whose egg is placed in the nest of ordinary birds. Of course, the newly hatched cuckoo eats all the food, leaving the ordinary siblings to starve to death.

00:15:29:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:29:030000.Dialogue: Luckily for you, that's where the metaphor ended.

00:15:33:100000.Speaker: Missy
00:15:33:100000.Dialogue: I thought it ended at cuckoo.

00:15:38:040000.Speaker: Missy
00:15:38:040000.Dialogue: You listen to me. If you want to start acting like a brother who cares about me, then terrific. Bring it on. But you try one time to tell me who I should be sleeping with, and you and I are going to go round and round the way we did when we were little. Remember?

00:15:59:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:59:050000.Dialogue: You donate eggs. We will place them in cryogenic storage. I will find an appropriate sperm donor for your eggs, have them fertilized and implanted in you. That way, everybody wins.

00:16:18:210000.Scene: The living room. Sheldon enters limping, holding his groin area.
00:16:18:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:18:210000.Dialogue: Correction. Missy can date whoever she wants.

00:16:24:100000.Speaker: Howard
00:16:24:100000.Dialogue: Look, we have to settle this.

00:16:26:010000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:26:010000.Dialogue: I agree. Sheldon's sister is hiding at Penny's because we've all been hitting on her at the same time.

00:16:30:070000.Speaker: Raj
00:16:30:070000.Dialogue: She's not hiding. She needed privacy to call her grandmother who's apparently very sick. And then I believe she has to wash her hair.

00:16:41:140000.Speaker: Howard
00:16:41:140000.Dialogue: You want to go again? Let's go.

00:16:46:220000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:46:220000.Dialogue: If we're going to fight over Missy, let's do it the right way. The honorable way. Take that! You want some more?

00:16:59:160000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:59:160000.Dialogue: And he's down! One, two, three...

00:17:09:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:09:120000.Dialogue: Nine, ten. Natural selection at work.

00:17:17:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:17:230000.Dialogue: Excuse me while I go tell Missy the good news.

00:17:33:080000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:33:080000.Dialogue: Nothing, just catching up. By the way, may I speak to Missy, please?

00:17:40:090000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:40:090000.Dialogue: Since you're leaving tomorrow, I was wondering if you'd like to go to dinner with me.

00:17:46:050000.Speaker: Missy
00:17:46:050000.Dialogue: That's so sweet. But no thanks.

00:17:51:130000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:51:130000.Dialogue: Do you have other plans or...

00:17:57:190000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:57:190000.Dialogue: All right. Enjoy the rest of your evening.

00:18:25:040000.Speaker: Howard
00:18:25:040000.Dialogue: I've come to call on Missy.

00:18:39:090000.Speaker: Howard
00:18:39:090000.Dialogue: Then you are in for a treat.

00:19:28:210000.Speaker: Penny
00:19:28:210000.Dialogue: Oh, honey. Is your medication wearing off?

00:19:35:060000.Speaker: Missy
00:19:35:060000.Dialogue: Well, hi, cutie pie. I was hoping you'd show up.

00:20:07:000000.Speaker: Missy
00:20:07:000000.Dialogue: We had a dog who made a noise like that. Had to put him down.

00:20:14:060000.Scene: The stairwell. Missy and Sheldon are descending.
00:20:14:060000.Speaker: Missy
00:20:14:060000.Dialogue: Any news you want me to pass on to Mom?

00:20:17:030000.Scene: The stairwell. Missy and Sheldon are descending.
00:20:17:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:20:17:030000.Dialogue: Well, she might be interested to know that I have refocused my research from bosonic string theory to heterotic string theory.

00:20:24:160000.Scene: The stairwell. Missy and Sheldon are descending.
00:20:24:160000.Speaker: Missy
00:20:24:160000.Dialogue: I'll just tell her you say hey.

00:20:29:100000.Scene: The stairwell. Missy and Sheldon are descending.
00:20:29:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:20:29:100000.Dialogue: Well, it was pleasant seeing you, other than that business with my testicles.

00:20:35:230000.Scene: The stairwell. Missy and Sheldon are descending.
00:20:35:230000.Speaker: Missy
00:20:35:230000.Dialogue: Come on, Shelly. I want you to know I'm very proud of you.

00:20:45:180000.Scene: The stairwell. Missy and Sheldon are descending.
00:20:45:180000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:20:46:160000.Scene: The stairwell. Missy and Sheldon are descending.
00:20:46:160000.Speaker: Missy
00:20:46:160000.Dialogue: Yep, I'm always bragging to my friends about my brother, the rocket scientist.
